first install=>
	sudo apt-get install git

configure git=>
	git config --global user.name "your user name"

	git config --global user.email "email_id"
create a local repository=>
	get init my_repository
	cd my_repository
	gedit readme
	gedit mycode.c
now add above two files in index..
	git add readme
	git add mycode.c
once we have made all changes we commit it
	git commit -m "some_massage"

now create aa repository on github
	git remote add origin https:github.com/user_name/my_repository.git
now push files
	git push origin master
